Here's how to create a new table with a specific name:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// Create a new table named "employees"
const employeesTable = sdb.newTable("employees");
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```

You can list all table names by calling the `logTableNames` method on the SimpleDB instance:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// Log all table names to the console
await sdb.logTableNames();
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```

After creating a table, you can use its methods like loadData to load CSV data.
```
