You can pass an array of table names to `selectTables`:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// Create and load data into multiple tables
const employeesTable = sdb.newTable("employees");
await employeesTable.loadData("./employees.csv");
const customersTable = sdb.newTable("customers");
await customersTable.loadData("./customers.csv");
const productsTable = sdb.newTable("products");
await productsTable.loadData("./products.csv");
// Select 'employees' and 'customers' tables
await sdb.selectTables(["employees", "customers"]);
// Close everything
await sdb.done();
```

