You can use an `if` statement to create the table only if it doesn't exist:

```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// Check if the table exists
const exists = await sdb.hasTable("employees");
if (!exists) {
  // Create the table because it doesn't exist
  const table = sdb.newTable("employees");
  console.log("Table created.");
} else {
  console.log("Table already exists.");
}
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```

